HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 116
By Hale
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend George McDonald on his
being named the 2024 Tennessee Farmer of the
Year.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that we salute those citizens who, through their extraordinary
efforts, have distinguished themselves as agricultural leaders of whom we can all be proud; and
WHEREAS, one such outstanding person is George McDonald, who was named the
2024 Tennessee Farmer of the Year by University of Tennessee Extension in coordination with
the Tennessee Farm Bureau Federation and was honored by the University of Tennessee
Institute of Agriculture at its annual Ag Day event in Knoxville on September 14, 2024; and
WHEREAS, Mr. McDonald was also honored to represent the State of Tennessee in the
thirty-fourth annual Southeastern Farmer of the Year competition at the Sunbelt Ag Expo in
Moultrie, Georgia, last October; and
WHEREAS, the Farmer of the Year Awards highlight each farmer's long and
distinguished career in such areas as ag production, marketing, business management, applied
research, environmental innovations, community service, and contributions to industry-related
organizations and their community; and
WHEREAS, the 1996 Tennessee Farmer of the Year, George McDonald, has a long and
storied career as a farmer, having known that he wanted to continue the farming legacy of his
family at a young age; and
WHEREAS, Mr. McDonald's Catesa Farms grows more than 9,000 acres of corn,
soybeans, wheat, milo, hay, watermelons, and strawberries, and in addition, he operates
Cumberland Valley Ag, which sells various necessities and stores crops for local producers; and
